subSubSection.paragraph:
Metathorax
: dorsally with a sparse line of hs, representing metatergal setae (mts) and dorsospiracular setae (dss). Ventral part of metapleural ridge (plr 
3
) short but well-sclerotised; metepisternum (eps 
3
) absent; metapleural ridge without either a metaprecoxal ridge or an additional short ridge extending ventrally from near coxal articulation. Metepimeron (epm 
3
) possibly represented by a pair of short sclerotised ridges that extend posteriorly above metacoxae. Ventrally with 1 pair hs anterior sternal setae (amss) and 2 pairs hs posterior metasternal setae (pmss) + 1 lp on each side. Metathoracic spiracle (sp 
3
): width of peritreme about 10–12 µm, with an associated lp. Metasternum (stn 
3
) unsclerotised.
